COUNTY WORKERS WIN AWARDS FROM ENERGY ENGINEERS 
Four staff members of the county Facilities Management Department have won 
awards in energy conservation from the Southern California chapter of the Assn. 
of Energy Engineers. 
The winners are Kenneth Hammer, Norm Hermreck, Thomas Schriber and Frank Work. 
Gregory Aden of Cushman &amp; Wakefield won the Energy Engineer of the Year 
award and Ted Bischak of the Irvine Office Co. won the Energy Manager of the 
Year award. 
